<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Dear Community:<P>I know there's been some discussion with regards to the new aggro rules that verant has implemented and its affect on pet classes such as the necro class.  <P>I wanted to get some feedback as to what some of you have been doing successfuly to keep your pet alive in group situations.  I am sure many of you have been chewing through pets at a much higher rate than you're accustomed too and have built a sufficient level of frustration with verant's newest change.<P>I've tried things such as setting my pet to no taunt, sending in my pet late (letting the other tanks build aggro) and chain casting my mend bones line to keep my pet alive.  Needless to say, i've had very little success with any of the above and wanted to see if anyone was having success using different methods.<P>Thanks in advance.<P>BTW: I've been hunting in Seb and IK of late.  Lose a pet in like 1 of 10 fights in seb and every other fight in IK.  Just stopped casting pet after the 5th cast (in IK).<P>--------------------<P><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55675" TARGET=_blank>Tencor Laureate - 60th Warlock</A>[br]<BR>Veil of Silence<BR>Innoruuk Server
