<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Definately turn taunt off if your pet isn't the meatshield, i'm quite sure it has less AC then a normal tank, would rather Shadowbond/Pact the main tank if needed then your pet. Personally i haven't found Mend Bones really usefull, in most groups i mem Pact of Shadows & Shadowbound, these 2 combined heals 850hps in 24 secs, which isn't bad at all  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> I find myself Vexing/healing pet quite often, the bugger gets alot of attention recently...<P>And finally like you said, sending pet a few secs after the fight as begun wouldnt hurt, and watch out the distance between pet and mob, if it's too short, it aggros to much. Another determinating factor is the Haste on pet, if the tanks has no haste maybe you should consider using the lvl 39 pet buff instead of the lvl 55 one if it's a prob<P>Last thing, i once heard that /pet sit down doesn't make the pet regen any faster, can someone comfirm this? I used to have my pet "med" in the low lvls but one day i read here that it doesn't change anything so i stopped<P>Spherik Darksavant<BR>Warlock of The Seventh Hammer
</FONT>
