<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
There just isn't any way to keep them alive any more other than dedicating a cleric to them.<P>Lightweight grind in the Hole earlier this week, nothing EVER took its eyes off the pet except to periodically pound the cleric. Even two AQed warriors, one of them with a damn Blade of the Black Dragon Eye, could not peel mobs off Boner for more than a single melee round.<P>Cleric just made a "/target pet" hotkey, CelHealed it at half and then Complete healed it. No one else ever required more than a top-off heal except me, because I was pulling. On mobs in their low 40s, this can be great depending on your group composition, but in higher level zones it means your pet becomes an expensive 2400 point rune for your main tank.<P>--------------------<P>--<BR>Retired Necromancer -- dead but dreaming<BR>Reckless Rogue -- doing the stuff they tell you not to try at home
