I think it's my fault.  I was telling all my friends how fun it was to snare a mob, then drop 4 dots on it, then keep backing up while my pet beat the crap out of it while it tried to get to me.  Hell, I even threw on Vampiric Embrace (123 dex helped with this), Grim Aura, and Shadow Vortex and TANKED for a while, hoping for a few procs.  Now, I have to fear it, and like someone said elsewhere, if the fear bounces, pet is almost dead before I can cast it again.<P>I started the necromancer for the times when I didn't have long enough to get a good group with my main, an enchanter.  Was going great, was always able to log on, fire up a pet, buff, and go kill blues, even black or yellow if I wanted to mana dump.  So much for that.  Success for me (at 25) is now dependent on Fear sticking, or me mana dumping on a blue mob so my pet doesn't die.<BR>No way I'm soloing yellows consistently anymore.   <P>This success dependency isn't much different than the enchanter's, so why don't I just go solo with the enchanter...  At least they're easier to get into groups when I have time.<P>I use to think people here were just *****ing and moaning, but if all the nerfs have been like this, I can see why you're furious.<P>Arnham<BR>25 Necromancer<BR>E'ci
