<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Gotta Agree with Verina,<P>This is a seriously Bad Nerf to Necros that actually brought alot to a group. Now instead of casting a Pet and replacing the spell gem with a Combat or Defensive spell, we are almost forced to keep the Pet spell dedicated to a gem. /sigh<P>But there is a plus side, the new aggro changes seem to have the mobs POUND a nearby medding Caster than a swinging tank. In a dire situation, if the cleric is LOM and the tank is almost dead, Vex a Mob, sit, get hit, sit, get hit,repeat. <P>The Mob seems to be more infuriated with the medding casters and immediately turns to him/her, allowing some free rounds on the mob by the tanks. I am not sure if this is consistant, but I used this trick when 5 friends and I took down the Named Totem in POG- Undogo Digolo.<P>Since it was only 6 of us, and that b#stard is unslowable and trips for 300+, I had to vex, sit down, take some shots, replenish HP and repeat to allow our cleric to regain enough mana to heal the tank and rogue.<P>So a HUGE /rude to Verant, thanks for another Nerf, but it won't stop us from being creative and playing a class we love.<P>Rulor X'Mortis
</FONT>
