<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Here's a few tricks i've been doing...<P>*Root the mob and have the main tank stand ontop of it.  With root on agro changes slightly, and mobs will prefer nearer targets even though it may have more hate for other targets that are still in reach.  I noticed this long time back, when a mob would agro a healer, it would immediately switch to the closest person meleeing it when it was rooted even though it was still in range to hit the healer.<P>*Let the other tanks get a head start always....<P>*Finally, having a pet with such intense agro on it isn't always a bad thing.  I would send my pet in when a tank needed a break, cast pact on him, then on pet...worked pretty well at keeping the clerics mana up.
</FONT>
